external_knowledge:
- "blossoms" metaphorically refers to "loan_id" or loan records; 
- "garden" symbolizes "bank_id" or bank entities;
- "seed capital" is used to metaphorically describe the "principal_amount" or initial loan amounts;
- "rainfall" is a metaphor for "interest_rate" or the interest applied to loans.

- 'Active loans' refer to loans that have not been paid off or defaulted;
- 'Recently active loans' implies loans that started or became active within a recent timeframe;
- 'Half-year' means a period of six months.

sql:
SELECT MIN(loan_term)
FROM loans
WHERE status != 'Paid Off' AND status != 'Default';

SELECT c.customer_name, la.status
FROM customers c
JOIN loan_applications la ON c.customer_id = la.customer_id;

SELECT DISTINCT loan_type_name 
FROM loan_types
WHERE minimum_term <= 12 AND maximum_term >= 12;

SELECT c.customer_name, la.application_id
FROM customers c
INNER JOIN loan_applications la ON c.customer_id = la.customer_id;
